LETTER XLIX.
The Hon. Mr. HARRINGTON to the Rev.
Mr. HOLMES.
BOSTON.
Accumulated
sorrows
continue to break over my devoted head.
Harriot
is at times deprived of her
reason
,
and we have no expectation of her
recovery
my
son
