prison
, where he had
wasted
his life, and he
sighed
to be again immured
within its walls.
SUCH is our
passion
for life; we love it
because
we know it; and our attachment
becomes
the more riveted, the longer we are
acquainted
with itOur
prison
grows familiar
we contemplate its horroursbut
however
gloomy the walls that
surround
us,
